Commerce Secretary C. William Veritycalled for stepped up coordination of the major industrializednations along the lines of the Venice pact last June whichcommitted the nations to coordinate economic policies.    Verity, speaking to a trade conference of the OverseasPrivate Investment Corp., said "We must improve coodination withour major industrialized allies and trading partners along thelines agreed to at the Venice meeting last June.    He added "we need better cooperation among advanceddeveloping countries in assuring responsibility to coordinatelocal economies commensurate with their economic resources. reuter&#3;